Quote:  Away back in 1929 wool manufacturers complained of a hairiness in New Zealand's Romney wool clip: large, straight and hairy fibres, 'halo hairs' projected above the fleece in the birthcoat of the lamb. Looking about for lambs with halo hairs, Dr Dry found a ram plentifully supplied with them.
